    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "Instructions\r\n----\r\n✅ **TO DO #1:** In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Internet.java</code>, write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getCountsByGroup()</code> method to return a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Results</code> object that stores the number of countries classified as high income, lower middle income, upper middle income, or other areas.\r\n\r\n1. If the group equals <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">\"High income\"</code>, increment the High Income counter by <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">1</code>.\r\n2. If the group equals <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">\"Lower middle income\"</code>, increment the Lower Middle Income counter by <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">1</code>.\r\n3. If the group equals <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">\"Upper middle income\"</code>, increment the Upper Middle Income counter by <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">1</code>.\r\n4. Otherwise, increment the Other counter by <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">1</code>.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #2:** In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">TheaterRunner.java</code>, call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getCountsByGroup()</code> method and then pass the result to the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">drawResults()</code> method.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> Check out the <strong>Help & Tips</strong> tab ⬆️ for help with writing multi-selection statements.\r\n</div>\r\n",
